16/08/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orban promised to help Hungarians in Serbia, mostly in aid to the education and information sectors.
On Saturday (August 14th), Orban visited Subotica at the invitation of Istvan Pastor, president of the Alliance of Vojvodina Hungarians.
Orban also said that his government will set aside funds to support the National Council of Hungarians in Serbia, which safeguards the cultural autonomy of Vojvodina's Hungarians.
(Tanjug, B92, Beta - 14/08/10)
